Class NodeBox.Node

  • java.lang.Object
    • javafx.scene.Node

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    javafx.css.Styleable, javafx.event.EventTarget
    Enclosing class:
    NodeBox

    public class NodeBox.Node
extends javafx.scene.layout.AnchorPane
    Node class. Every NodeBox must have one Node. A node is responsible to control the Input/Output buttons and the icon which represents the node functionality. Do not mix this name with a node Graph! there's nothing to do with it and much less with the Java's Node (javafx.scene.Node).
